# 🎰 SlotGame .NET API

A production-style Slot Machine backend built with **ASP.NET Core 9** and **PostgreSQL**.

The project simulates a real online casino slot game with secure random number generation, JWT authentication, transactional balance updates, idempotent requests, and Docker support.

---

## 🚀 Features

- 🎰 Slot machine game engine
- 🎲 Cryptographically secure RNG
- 💰 Player balance management
- 🏆 Paylines & Paytable evaluation
- 🔒 JWT Authentication
- 🔁 Idempotent Spin API
- 🗄️ PostgreSQL + Entity Framework Core
- 🐳 Docker & Docker Compose
- 📄 Swagger / OpenAPI
- 🧪 Clean Architecture
- ⚡ Dependency Injection
- 📦 Entity Framework Migrations

---

# 🛠 Tech Stack

| Technology | Description |
|------------|-------------|
| ASP.NET Core 9 | Web API |
| C# | Backend Language |
| Entity Framework Core | ORM |
| PostgreSQL | Database |
| Docker | Containerization |
| Docker Compose | Local Development |
| JWT | Authentication |
| Swagger | API Documentation |

---

# 📂 Project Structure

```
SlotGame
│
├── SlotGame.Api              # ASP.NET Core Web API
├── SlotGame.Core             # Game Engine & Business Logic
├── SlotGame.Infrastructure   # Database & EF Core
```

---

# ⚙️ Getting Started

## Clone repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/slotgame-dotnet-api.git
cd slotgame-dotnet-api
```

---

## Configure Environment

Create a `.env` file in the project root.

```env
POSTGRES_USER=slotuser
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=your_password
POSTGRES_DB=SlotGame

JWT_SIGNING_KEY=your_secret_key
JWT_ISSUER=SlotGame.Api
JWT_AUDIENCE=SlotGame.Client
```

---

## Run with Docker

```bash
docker compose up --build
```

The API will be available at:

```
http://localhost:8080
```

Swagger:

```
http://localhost:8080/swagger
```

---

# Database Migration

Create migration

```bash
dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate \
--project SlotGame.Infrastructure \
--startup-project SlotGame.Api
```

Update database

```bash
dotnet ef database update \
--project SlotGame.Infrastructure \
--startup-project SlotGame.Api
```

---

# Authentication

Login endpoint

```
POST /api/Auth/login
```

Example Request

```json
{
    "playerId": "YOUR_PLAYER_ID"
}
```

Response

```json
{
    "token": "JWT_TOKEN",
    "expiresAt": "2026-01-01T12:00:00Z"
}
```

---

# Spin API

Endpoint

```
POST /api/Spin
```

Headers

```
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN
```

Request

```json
{
    "betAmount": 10,
    "idempotencyKey": "GUID"
}
```

Example Response

```json
{
    "grid": [],
    "betAmount": 10,
    "totalWin": 25,
    "winningLines": [],
    "newBalance": 115
}
```

